               <head>(pastedowns only) Job glossed</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="St_Johns_College_MS_157-item1">
                     <note>This modern MS, which begins with an Oxford disputation and sermon, both
                        dated <date when="1540">1540</date>, contains medieval binding
                        materials:</note>
                     <title key="work_12443" type="desc">Job</title>
                     <note>5:16–18 (the rear pastedown) and 6:11–22 <locus from="ir" to="ii v">(fols.
                              i–ii<hi rend="superscript">v</hi></locus>; the leaf has been bound
                        backwards), with the ordinary gloss (<bibl><ref target="http://www.repbib.uni-trier.de/cgi-bin/rebiIndex.tcl?ac=searchlist&amp;tlnr=11800">Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 11800</ref> [9:485–6])</bibl>. There
                        are a few early marginal notes on <locus from="ii r" to="ii r">fol.
                        ii</locus>, and a good many pen-trials, <date calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1510" notBefore="1490">s. xv/xvi</date>, on <locus from="ii v" to="ii v">fol. ii<hi rend="superscript">v</hi></locus> and the rear
                        pastedown (upside down).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>Vellum.</support>
                        <extent>Fols. <measure quantity="2" type="leaf">2</measure> (numbered fols.
                           i–ii, the raised front pastedown; and the unnumbered rear
                              pastedown).<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height quantity="200">200 surviving mm</height>
                              <width quantity="176">176 surviving</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>(the larger leaf at the front).</note>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout writtenLines="22 45">The writing covers most of the leaves (an
                           intact leading edge on the front, the large lower margin on the rear
                           leaf): a text column <dimensions type="column" unit="mm">
                              <width max="45" min="30">30–45</width>
                           </dimensions> mm wide, set into a gloss column <dimensions type="gloss" unit="mm">
                              <width max="85" min="70">70–85</width>
                           </dimensions> mm wide. At the fullest, 22+ surviving lines of text, 45
                           lines of gloss. Prickings on the front leaf; some bounds in brown ink,
                           the rules apparently in lead.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
